### Describe the bug

I'm trying to use a Nuget package component in a Blazor Web + WASM page. It works in debug mode, but when publishing I get a browser console error saying Error: AggregateException_ctor_DefaultMessage (The parameter 'data' with type 'BlazorCharts.PlotDataModels.PieSeries' in assembly 'BlazorCharts' could not be found.)

I tried InteractiveServer mode publish, and there it worked too.

I also copied the library code to my project, and that worked too after publishing.

### Expected Behavior

I would expect the library component to work in WASM after publishing too.
I guess this is somehow related to trimming, although the library doesn't use any reflection (it's a razor class library, source here: https://github.com/Markz878/BlazorCharts).

### Steps To Reproduce

1. Create a new Blazor Web project with WASM interactivity per component (no sample pages)
2. Install "BlazorSVGCharts" Version="1.1.9" on both the client and server.
3. Create a new component Charts.razor in the WASM client project with this markdown:
```
@using BlazorCharts
@using BlazorCharts.PlotDataModels
<PieChart Data="data" Title="Pie Chart" Width=300 Height=300 FontSize="10px" FontColor="rgb(40,40,40)" EdgeThickness="0.5" Animate=false/>
@code {
    [Parameter][EditorRequired] public required PieSeries data { get; set; }
}
```
4. Put this markdown in the Home.razor in the server project:
```
@page "/"
@using BlazorCharts.PlotDataModels
<PageTitle>Home</PageTitle>
@if (data is not null)
{
    <div style="width: 600px;">
        <Charts data="@data" @rendermode="RenderMode.InteractiveWebAssembly" />
    </div>
}

@code {
    private PieSeries? data;

    protected override void OnInitialized()
    {
        data = new PieSeries(true,
        new PieItem("Red item", 30, "rgba(255,0,0,0.75)", "black", new List<string>() { "Red Tooltip Line 1", "Red Tooltip Line 2" }),
        new PieItem("Green item", 55, "rgba(0,255,0,0.75)", "black", new List<string>() { "Green Tooltip Line 1", "Green Tooltip Line 2" }),
        new PieItem("Blue item", 42, "rgba(0,0,255,0.75)", "black", new List<string>() { "Blue Tooltip Line 1", "Blue Tooltip Line 2" })
    );
    }
}
```
5. Run the project in debug mode and see it working (tooltips appear when hovering over the chart)
6. Publish the project with dotnet publish, run the resulting exe, open in browser and see the error described above.

