## Background and Motivation

It would be great if the `Microsoft.Net.Http.Headers.HeaderNames` class could also contain a constant for the "Content-Id" header so developers don't need to rely on custom constants prone to typos.

## Proposed API

```diff
namespace Microsoft.Net.Http.Headers;

public static class HeaderNames
{
+    public static readonly string ContentId = "Content-Id";
}
```

## Usage Examples

```csharp
using System;
using Microsoft.Net.Http.Headers;

Console.WriteLine(HeaderNames.ContentId); // prints "Content-Id"
```

As a reference, [MimeKit has this](http://www.mimekit.net/docs/html/P_MimeKit_MimeEntity_ContentId.htm).

